snippet.textDisplay:
Look, let's be real about this. The fact that the Clippers have done as well as they have with Kawhi and Paul George missing several games, is evidence that the team's chemistry hangs on Pat Bev, Harrell and Williams!! That team is just scary with those three guys on the floor together. As great a player Jordon was, try to imagine the Bulls winning 6 championships without Rodman, Scottie and Steve Kerr. That's real hard to imagine and Kawhi is no MJ, not even close. But take Lebron out the game for a few minutes and we all know what happens.
I think the post season is gonna come down to Frank Vogel vs Doc Rivers.

snippet.textDisplay:
hmm...Skip makes a very interesting point. Clippers have been on a rampage. Odds of them experiencing a 'regression to the mean'; or a 'scheduled loss' in (nba terms) continuous challenging games increase. on the other hand -- i also like the idea of lakers being doubted because they've had less rest than the clippers (clippers have an extra day of rest, and a less challenging opponent in rockets v. bucks). that said, i think what chris said in the first argument made more sense: lakers might sacrifice this game in order to get the final match up in april...and in the playoffs, when bron turns it all the way up, clippers will be stunned.


this lakers' team isn't full of chokers and people that just stand around waiting for him to play. caruso's a dog. bradley's a dog. ad is a monster; clutch in the paint and from midrange (and also he makes FTs at a high clip). clippers are great defensively but they're also super aggressive and as it gets closer to the post-season, refs are a lot more attentive...all that being said, i don't know if i want to pick against the clippers in this game.


i would like it if the lakers would surprise everyone and go 2-0 against the presumed best teams in the league (bucks/clippers)...i also don't trust kawhi leonard to show up when the stars are the brightest ... i don't know if paul george can hit his 3 consistently...i don't think it'll be a good game for some reason
